# FANUC Dataset Reference Rule

The dataset at `fanuc_dataset/normalized/` is canon. These guidelines apply whenever you are drafting a spec, a review, an ingestion entry, or a normalized file.

## Find

Prefer `fanuc_knowledge.search` over filesystem grep. It handles synonyms, topic tags, and respects the frontmatter.

- Keyword lookup: `fanuc_knowledge.search(query="PNS handshake")`.
- Topic lookup: `fanuc_knowledge.list_by_tag(tag="motion")`.
- Neighbor lookup: `fanuc_knowledge.related(id="FANUC_REF_J_Motion")`.

When offline or MCP is unavailable: search `fanuc_dataset/DATASET_INDEX.md`, then the appropriate subdirectory.

## Cite

Every non-trivial claim in a spec or review cites the entry by `id`:

```markdown
Speed override is applied at program entry via `R[90:OVERRIDE]` (source: `FANUC_REF_Override_Register`).
```

Multiple citations: comma-separated list, in source-tier order (T1 vendor manual first, T3 community last). If two entries conflict, document under `## Discrepancies` in your output.

## Compose

- Reference entries first, examples second, articles last. Reference tells you the truth; examples show a shape; articles give context.
- Protocol entries (`protocols/`) are the authoritative fieldbus / integration patterns. Always consult before specifying I/O tables.
- Safety entries (`safety/`) are the ONLY source for ISO 10218, ISO/TS 15066, and DCS rules. Never rely on examples or articles for a safety claim.

## Do NOT

- Paraphrase long passages from vendor manuals. Cite and summarize. Short literal quotes (<=30 words) are acceptable for precision.
- Promote a `customer_programs/**/integration_notes/` note into a spec claim. Those are customer-scoped context.
- Create new normalized entries by hand. Use the `ingest-pdf-to-normalized` or research workflows so the QA agent validates frontmatter.

## Entry navigation

Each normalized file has YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
id: FANUC_REF_J_Motion
title: TP Joint Motion Instruction
topic: motion
fanuc_controller: [R-30iB, R-30iB Plus]
system_sw_version: [V9.30, V9.40]
language: TP
source:
  type: vendor_manual
  title: "FANUC R-30iB V9 Operator's Manual"
  pages: [180, 195]
  tier: T1
license: reference-only
revision_date: 2026-04-21
related: [FANUC_REF_L_Motion, FANUC_REF_Termination_Types]
difficulty: intermediate
---
```

The `id` is what you cite. `related:` points to neighbors. `tier:` tells you how much weight to give the claim.

## Dataset update request

If research uncovers a gap, open a dataset-entry ticket via the knowledge-ingestion workflow rather than fabricating an answer. Missing entries are tracked in `research/RESEARCH_TRACKING.md`.
